updatesFromCustomers.text:
I was already very fond of Indonesian food.
But this.... This is very different from what I had before. Not spicy, but delicious complex flavours. Delicious!

reviews.name: Ni Lo-Va
reviews.text: Beautiful and homy restaurant away from the Ubud center and noise, with some art and garden pathways. Soft Balinese music on the background. A lot of different Balinese options on the menu. We chose some tuna with spicy sauce, which was very tasty, and not too spicy (hot) at all. Also the fresh fruit juices were tasty, with a hint of lime. Our dessert crepes were mostly made of coconut. Sweet, but not too sweet. Just perfect! We'll definitely go back.
reviews.textTranslated: Restoran yang indah dan nyaman, jauh dari pusat Ubud dan kebisingan, dengan beberapa karya seni dan jalan setapak di taman. Musik Bali yang lembut diputar di latar belakang. Banyak pilihan hidangan Bali yang berbeda di menu. Kami memilih tuna dengan saus pedas, yang sangat enak, dan tidak terlalu pedas sama sekali. Jus buah segarnya juga enak, dengan sedikit rasa jeruk nipis. Crepes hidangan penutup kami sebagian besar terbuat dari kelapa. Manis, tapi tidak terlalu manis. Sempurna! Kami pasti akan kembali.

good service..
Luarbiasa sih, waitersnya mau banget degan sabar dan sopan melayani kami foto² disini... kasih surprice buat yg ulang tahun. Tempatnya aestethic banget buat foto², setiap sudut nya cantik, mewah dan bersih. Untuk makanan lumayan.... review jujur masakan indoesia tapi lebih terasa western nya, mungkin banyak expatriat yaa yg berkunjung, jd disesuaikan.

reviews.name: Fritzgerald Merle
reviews.text:
Splendid meal experience at Plataran Menteng - our first meal in Jakarta. Service from Sam was excellent and exemplary. Dishes recommended tingled our palates and thoroughly satisfied our appetites and craving for exotic sambals and Flavours of Indonesia.
After lunch Sam showed us around the beautiful and artfully maintained mansion and the various dining room options for private gatherings. A great experience all in !
reviews.textTranslated:
Pengalaman bersantap yang luar biasa di Plataran Menteng - santapan pertama kami di Jakarta. Pelayanan dari Sam sangat baik dan patut dicontoh. Hidangan yang direkomendasikan menggugah selera dan benar-benar memuaskan nafsu makan serta keinginan kami akan sambal eksotis dan cita rasa Indonesia.
Setelah makan siang, Sam mengajak kami berkeliling rumah besar yang indah dan terawat dengan apik serta berbagai pilihan ruang makan untuk acara pribadi. Pengalaman yang luar biasa secara keseluruhan!

reviews.name: Dyah Galuh
reviews.text: Very good venue for business lunches and coffee meetings with friends. Foods n drinks are great, service excellent. Only issue is parking, like most restaurants within the area.
reviews.textTranslated: Tempat yang sangat bagus untuk makan siang bisnis dan pertemuan minum kopi dengan teman-teman. Makanan dan minumannya enak, pelayanannya sangat baik. Satu-satunya masalah adalah parkir, seperti kebanyakan restoran di area ini.

reviews.name: Nanang Zulkarnain
reviews.text:
Every spot was so aesthetic! Beneran takjub dengan interior dan setiap sudut Plataran Menteng. Sampai bingung mau foto di mana lagi.

Toilet-nya pun mewah dan aduhai indahnya.

Soal rasa dan visual makanan, ga perlu ragu lagi.

reviews.name: Kamela Amara
reviews.text: Been here a couple of times with friends and family. The service is always friendly and attentive, and the food is BOMB 💣 it’s been very good every time. One of the best Indonesian food I’ve had in Bali (and I’m Indonesian, so you know it’s legit). Would definitely visit again. My mum loves the mie goreng so much she stole it off my plate lol🥰
reviews.textTranslated: Saya sudah beberapa kali ke sini bersama teman dan keluarga. Pelayanannya selalu ramah dan penuh perhatian, dan makanannya ENAK BANGET 💣 selalu enak setiap kali. Salah satu makanan Indonesia terbaik yang pernah saya makan di Bali (dan saya orang Indonesia, jadi Anda tahu ini asli). Pasti akan berkunjung lagi. Ibu saya sangat menyukai mie gorengnya sampai-sampai dia mengambilnya dari piring saya lol🥰
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Hi Kamela Amara,

Thank you so much for coming back to Dapoer Asia couple of times with your friends and family !
We’re really happy to hear that you enjoyed the friendly service also we’re so attentive and loved the food every time. Hearing that it’s one of the best Indonesian foods you’ve had in Bali. Especially coming from an Indonesian, that’s means a lot to us. 

And we’re are so surprised and happy to hear that your mum stealing the Mie Goreng off your plate these means your mum loved so much our Mie Goreng. 

We can’t wait to welcome you and your family back again soon!

Enjoy a pleasant journey and delicious dishes. 

Best,
The Dapoer Asia Team.

reviews.name: Sarah S
reviews.text: I’ve ordered from here quite a few times and it used to be a reliable go-to for Indonesian food nearby. The last takeaway was disappointing though, the gado-gado tasted off and I couldn’t finish it.
reviews.textTranslated: Saya sudah beberapa kali memesan dari sini dan dulu tempat ini selalu menjadi pilihan andalan untuk makanan Indonesia di dekat sini. Namun, pesanan terakhir saya mengecewakan, gado-gado-nya terasa aneh dan saya tidak bisa menghabiskannya.
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Sarah S,

My name is George and I am the owner of Dapoer Asia.
Thank you so much for choosing Dapoer Asia for few times as a loyal customer and also place for you to enjoy our Food and Beverage. 

First of all, I would like to apologize for the inconvenience. Our first priority is put fully respect for all our loyal customers. On behalf of my team at Dapoer Asia, I would like to apologize for our products which has not met your expectations.

Regarding your order the Gado Gado menu which tasted off. It's regrettable because Gado Gado is one of our favorite menu at Dapoer Asia. Because the basic seasoning for Gado Gado is Vegetables, Boiled Eggs, Potatoes, Tofu, Tempe and Peanut Sauce, and the level of spiciness for the Gado Gado is "Not Spicy/ Slightly Spicy/ Normal/ Spicy/ Very Spicy". 
Could you please explain in more details what the Gado Gado tasted off? 
It would be not fair for us if you don't provide us a summary of your dissatisfaction with our food, mentioned : that your last take away was disappointing because the food had no tasted that you couldn't finish it.

Please do not hesitate, if you feel like trying us again one day, feel free to contact me. We do hope to see you again in the not too distant future. We would all be delighted to have you experience the real Dapoer Asia and to have you leave us with the fond memories we are known for creating. If you don’t mind please contact me by email : dapoerasia.bali@gmail.com or leave your message by WhatsApp to this number +62 812 8477 7887. 

I would very much like to have a private conversation with you. I hope to hear from you soon. 

With kind regards,
George and the team at Dapoer Asia
